cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of monocular 3D reconstruction of deformable objects using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the use of domain-specific loss functions and the generalizability of the proposed approach, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed approach has potential applications in interventional diagnostics and augmented reality, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
